Experimental !

sprite2css - A tool to generate CSS rules for sprite locations on spritesheets.
This code uses the HTML5 FileReader API and has only been 'tested' on Firefox (13, 14) and Chrome (whatever version they're up to atm.)

Requirements:

- (local) server like Apache etc. to get get the image upload working
- you may need to set folder permissions for the upload folder depending on your OS

How to use:

1. Drag & drop image file to grid
2. Specify ID or class name to be used for the box to be placed
3. Specify dimensions of the box you want to place
4. Optional. Toggle snap mode for the next box
5. Click 'Add new box'
6. Reposition new box. (Always spawns top/left)
7. Resize box if needed.

Controls:

- move boxes on grid via drag & drop
- resize boxes via the resize handlers at each box's bottom/right corner(s)
- double click a box to remove it from the grid
- hover over a box to highlight the corresponding CSS section in the right panel
- hover over a CSS rule in the right panel to highlight the corresponding box on the grid 

